race.comment: KINGS VALLEY (1) has had a few chances without breaking through this time in but does look well placed again, trying hard behind the talented Gilded Water here last time out when third. Should be at peak fitness now at his second 2000m run for the campaign and maps for every chance with Zahra on from barrier two. FEDERER (6) sprinted best off an even tempo to bounce back to form at Flemington last start, winning an easier race. Drops in weight off that and might be able to go on with it. GOLDEN CENTURY (2) comes down from NSW in flying form, winning his past two impressively. This is harder but must respect Waller bringing him here and his upside. LITZDEEL (7) has been solid in two runs back and will be fitter for them. She may want even further now but has claims. ARGENTUM (3) can be an improver second up.
